## Requirements

- Node.js 20.9 or newer
- npm, pnpm, yarn, or bun

## Environment Setup

Copy or rename the environment template before running the app:

```bash
cp .env.example .env
```

Open `.env` and fill in the values required by your selected modules.

<% if (hasMongoDB) { -%>
### MongoDB

Set `MONGODB_URI` in `.env` before using database features. The generated `.env.example` includes a local MongoDB URL that you can replace with your own connection string.

<% } -%>
<% if (hasAuth) { -%>
### Better Auth And Google OAuth

Set these values in `.env` before signing in with Google:

- `BETTER_AUTH_URL`
- `BETTER_AUTH_SECRET`
- `GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID`
- `GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET`

Better Auth uses MongoDB in this starter, so keep `MONGODB_URI` configured as well.

<% } -%>
## Install Dependencies

```bash
npm install
```

## Run Locally

```bash
npm run dev
```

Open [http://localhost:3000](http://localhost:3000) in your browser.

<% if (hasMongoDB) { -%>
